name: Dry Mesic
desciption: Ecoregion with a minimal supply of moisture.
:LABEL: WaterPreference

name: Hydric
desciption: Ecoregion in which soil is permanently or seasonally saturated by water.
:LABEL: WaterPreference

name: In Water
desciption: Ecoregion in which water is predominant medium.
:LABEL: WaterPreference

name: Mesic
desciption: Ecoregion with a moderate or well-balanced supply of moisture.
:LABEL: WaterPreference

name: Wet Mesic
desciption: Ecoregion with over-abundant supply of moisture.
:LABEL: WaterPreference

name: Xerix
desciption: Ecoregion receiving less than 250 millimetres of rain and evaporation exceeding rainfall.
:LABEL: WaterPreference
